register.description: AMP Mode peripheral mapping register. When the register bit is '0' the peripheral is mapped into the 0x2000000 address range using AXI bus 5 from the Coreplex. register.description: AMP context A. When the register bit is '0' the peripheral is not allowed access from context A.

register.description: AMP context B. When the register bit is '0' the peripheral is not allowed access from context B.

register.description: When the register bit is '0' hart is not associated with context A.

register.description: When the register bit is '0' hart is not associated with context B.
register.name: CONTEXT_B_HART_EN

register.description: Way indexes less than or equal to this register value may be used by the cache. E.g. set to 0x7, will allocate 8 cache ways, 0-7 to cache, and leave 8-15 as LIM. Note 1: Way 0 is always allocated as cache. Note 2: each way is 128KB.

register.description: Way mask register master DMA. Set field to zero to disable way from this master. The available cache ways are 0 to number set in WAY_ENABLE register. If using scratch pad memory, the ways you want reserved for scrathpad are not available for selection, you must set to 0. e.g. If three ways reserved for scratchpad, WAY_MASK_0, WAY_MASK_1 and WAY_MASK_2 will be set to zero for all masters, so they can not evict the way.

register.description: Indicates if eMMC is configured for use (bit 0 == 1), If SD is configued for use (bit 1 == 1). Bit 2 indicates which one should be used by default on MSS embedded software startup ( bit2 == 0, implies default is eMMC, bit2 == 1, implies default is SD). The eMMC configuration is always defined in xml tag (io_mux, the SD configuration is always defined in xml tag (io_mux_alt). All other elements in the (o_mux) and (io_mux_alt) not releating to eMMC/SD differences should be the same values.
